Class DistanceCapacityInterface

java.lang.Object
core.NetworkInterface
interfaces.DistanceCapacityInterface
All Implemented Interfaces:
ModuleCommunicationListener
public class DistanceCapacityInterface extends NetworkInterface
A Network Interface that that takes in to account he distance from the other (connected) interface when determining the capacity of the links. The distance-dependent transmission speeds are given as comma-separated values using setting TRANSMIT_SPEEDS_S.

  • Field Details

    • TRANSMIT_SPEEDS_S

      public static final String TRANSMIT_SPEEDS_S
      Comma-separated list of speed values -setting id ("transmitSpeeds" ). The first value is the speed at distance 0 and the following are speeds at equal steps until the last one is the speed at the end of the transmit range ( NetworkInterface.TRANSMIT_RANGE_S). The speed between the steps is linearly interpolated.
